* Generics was introduced in JAVA 5

Issues before java Generics-----
-> Type safety
-> Manual casting
-> No compile time checking

/*  -- issue before generics --
        ArrayList list = new ArrayList();
            // pehle hum kuch bhi add kara dete the, and fir user
            // bhi kuch bhi acces karta tha, and fir manually typecasting karke data lena padta tha
        list.add(23);
        list.add("Hello");
        list.add("Generics");

        String s = (String) list.get(0); // humne yaha integer data ko String me typecast kiya hai
        System.out.println(s);
*/

----Naming Convention----
While you can name type parameters anything, the convention is to use single letters that describe the purpose of the type parameter:

T: Type
E: Element (used in collections)
K: Key (used in maps)
V: Value (used in maps)
N: Number